data.content:
Here are the three breaking changes affecting your code in EF Core 10, with fixes:

---

## 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` — now takes a regular lambda, not an expression tree

Your expression-tree manipulation **won't compile** because the parameter changed from `Expression<Func<...>>` to `Func<...>`.

**Fix** — replace the entire block with:

```csharp
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

No more manual `Expression.Call`/`Expression.Lambda` needed.

---

## 2. Complex type columns are now uniquified + nested paths use full path

Two sub-changes:
- **Same-name properties** (e.g. `ShippingAddress.Street` and `BillingAddress.Street`) now get distinct column names (`Street` vs `Street1`) instead of silently sharing one column.
- **Nested complex types** now prefix with the full path: `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` maps to `Payment_BillingAddress_City` instead of the old `BillingAddress_City`.

**Fix** — if you have existing tables, pin the old column names explicitly:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress, p =>
        p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress, p =>
        p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
});

// For nested complex types, pin old names:
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>()
    .ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment)
    .ComplexProperty(p => p.BillingAddress)
    .Property(a => a.City)
    .HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City");
```

Or generate a new migration to adopt the new column names.

---

## 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` — new `logCommandText` parameter

All methods (`CommandReaderExecuting`, `CommandReaderExecuted`, etc.) now require an additional `string logCommandText` parameter (contains redacted SQL for logging).

**Fix:**

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection,
        DbCommand command,
        DbContext context,
        Guid commandId,
        Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)   // ← new parameter
    {
        // Use logCommandText for logging (sensitive data redacted)
        // Use command.CommandText for actual execution SQL
    }
}
```

Update all other method signatures on the interface similarly.
